article.headline: UALR 62, Arkansas St. 60
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- D'Andre Williams scored 18 points and Arkansas-Little Rock defeated Arkansas State 62-60 Saturday night. Tramar Sutherland's two free throws with less than a second remaining won it for the Trojans (15-15, 12-4). UALR clinched the Sun Belt's West Division title and will be the No. 2 seed for the conference tournament that begins March 3 in Hot Springs, Ark. Courtney Jackson scored 12 points and Will Neighbour had 10 rebounds for UALR, which rallied from a 12-point deficit in the second half. Marcus Hooten led the Red Wolves (12-18, 6-9) with 18 points. Trey Finn scored 12 for Arkansas State. UALR won the earlier meeting, 63-62 last month in Jonesboro.
